items.title: Market marginally lower in volatile week; rupee depreciates
items.description: In this week, the Indian rupee ended lower against the US dollar as it fell 82 paise at 86.05 per dollar on April 11 against the April 4 closing of 85.23.

items.title: Wall Street ends whipsaw week sharply higher as Fed comments soothe market
items.description: The Dow Jones Industrial Average rose 619.05 points, or 1.56%, to 40,212.71, the S&P 500 gained 95.31 points, or 1.81%, to 5,363.36 and the Nasdaq Composite gained 337.15 points, or 2.06%, to 16,724.46.
